The paper deals with image retargeting, which involves manipulating the visual content of an image while preserving its semantic structure. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM), as well as graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since it requires deep learning techniques and semantic understanding of the image content. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for image retargeting, which involves a coarse-to-fine approach that involves searching and fusing nearest neighbor fields. This approach is related to machine learning (cs.LG) since it involves optimizing a model to generate the best retargeting results.
